- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper uses a two-dimensional legged robot as an example to illustrate the model, which suggests a connection to robotics. 
- cs.SI (Systems and Control): The time-stepping algorithm developed in the paper involves the conservation of continuous energy and discrete momentum, which is a topic in systems and control. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves the development of a computational model for simulating impacts, which falls under the domain of computational engineering. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): While not the main focus of the paper, the time-stepping algorithm developed in the paper involves the use of algorithms and data structures.
